commits.message: Update build command
iterate

Use accurate token counts (#1024)

* Use accurate token counts

The `total` token count is now based upon an identical format
conversation sent to the LLM during response generation.

This results in counts that should be accurate, and prevent token limit
errors entirely.

* Match token counts precisely, and add baseline count

* Calculate `total` as summation of other section token counts

* add message to response if it ended when token limit exceeded, no translations

---------

Fix race in credentials polling (#1042)

Previously the assumption here was that this path is locked & safe
when there is a furnished github cred in the system. However, when the
user logs out, the `unwrap()` call can blow up the task, and
this may cause issues.

* allow paid users sync branches

* Fix clippy features

* Disable branch switching for local repos

* cloud implies pro

* Update dockerfile

pull_request.title: Improve tooltip for generate button
pull_request.body:
The generate button can be disabled for a number of reasons:
- Token limit exceeded
- No value in input
- File change wasn't saved (selected line ranges changed or new file added)
- Some context files are not available (e.g. the repo was removed or is in an indexing state)
For the last reason, the tooltip was the same as for token limit exceeded. Now it should have the correct message.

release.name: v0.5.7
release.body:
## What's Changed
* Add binary extensions to blacklist by @Dead4W in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1050
* Remove failures from time management by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1052
* Filter entries that are neither files nor directories by @calyptobai in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1056
* Prioritize removal of repositories in the queue by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1046
* Remove tantivy global reader lock by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1053
* [Blo-1762] prompt selection by @rmuller-ml in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1045
* Update tauri to 1.5.0 by @anastasiya1155 in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1058
* Check if index directory exists before deleting by @ggordonhall in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1061
* Don't use credentials to fetch public repos by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1048
* Escape regex string in search-based ref/def navigation by @ggordonhall in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1060
* Upload symbols to Sentry by @ggordonhall in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1063
* Don't show indexing state on code studio cards by @anastasiya1155 in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1055
* Bump `/src-tauri` Sentry by @ggordonhall in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1066
* Allow force indexing files in the app by @anastasiya1155 in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1062
* Refresh cognito config from public API by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1065
* Catch unwind file indexing iterator by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1057
* Improve error logging on status changes by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1068
* Refactor credentials handling by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1067
* Limit maximum number of steps, not exchanges by @calyptobai in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1073
* Synchronicity issues with login flows by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1074
* Remove trust dns by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1076
* Recover from network errors in `poll_for_oauth_token` by @ggordonhall in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1078
* Increase rlimit by @ggordonhall in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1080
* Bump `esaxx-rs` fork to 0.1.10 by @calyptobai in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1082
* Improve qdrant logging to observe crashes in sentry by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1071
* Fix panic analytics by @calyptobai in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1081
* Use arrows to navigate between selected ranges in code studio by @anastasiya1155 in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1075
* Update version to 0.5.7 by @ggordonhall in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1084
* Better server polling by @anastasiya1155 in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1083
* Build binaries if building for cloud by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1088
* Move tutorial questions to first message by @anastasiya1155 in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1070
* Disable back/forward keyboard navigation if user is typing by @anastasiya1155 in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1077
* Add query logs by @ggordonhall in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1089
* Update to non-symlinky git by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1090
* Remove interactive cred checks by @rsdy in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1091

## New Contributors
* @Dead4W made their first contribution in https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/pull/1050

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/BloopAI/bloop/compare/v0.5.6...v0.5.7

Remove interactive cred updates (#1091)

This introduces very unpredictible behaviour in the webserver

pull_request.title: Remove interactive cred checks
pull_request.body: Seems like putting this on the request path will intermittently cause network-related hangs, and blocks requests. It's better to solely rely on some mechanism to fire early if we detect there's a hang.
